{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Approved and merged to main","closed_at":"2026-03-04T03:38:24Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"3734d5383686c9c7cd7a713e9fe8812d7dfcacd430f0b2aeef77f358f89ed326","created_at":"2026-03-03T14:48:04Z","created_by":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Implement a single-page HTML/CSS/JS admin console served at GET / by the admin server.\n\nFile: nanobot/admin/static/index.html (bundled as package data)\n\nUI Sections:\n1. API Keys — list all LLM providers; show key presence (masked); inline edit field to update; save button per row\n2. Chat Integrations — list all channels (Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, etc.); toggle enabled; expand to reveal and edit config fields; save per channel\n3. MCP Servers — table of configured servers; Add button (dialog with name, command/args or URL fields); Edit and Delete per row\n4. Agent Settings — form for model, provider, temperature, max_tokens, max_tool_iterations, memory_window, reasoning_effort; single Save button\n\nDesign requirements:\n- Vanilla HTML5 + CSS + JavaScript (no build step, no frameworks)\n- Bearer token prompt on first load if admin token is configured (stored in sessionStorage for convenience)\n- Token lifecycle rules (MUST follow exactly):\n  (a) Auth is always enforced server-side — the UI stores the token only for UX convenience, never as a security gate\n  (b) Every fetch() call sends the stored token in the Authorization header; if the server returns 401, the UI MUST immediately re-prompt for the token (do not show an opaque error or hide the UI)\n  (c) Never add a client-side gate that hides the UI or skips rendering based on whether a token is stored — all protection comes from the server's 401 responses\n- fetch() API for all REST calls\n- Inline save feedback (green checkmark / red error message)\n- Responsive layout (works on desktop and mobile)\n- Clean, minimal design matching nanobot's aesthetic (dark-friendly, use system fonts)\n\nTesting:\n- Manual smoke test (no automated unit test for pure HTML — integration covered by API tests)\n- Update pyproject.toml [tool.hatch.build] include to bundle nanobot/admin/static/** files","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"Bantu-3j8","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"teakwood.dev@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Feature: Admin web UI single-page frontend","updated_at":"2026-03-04T03:38:24Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
