{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Approved and merged to main","closed_at":"2026-03-03T17:12:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"efd0abbf4b5154f32a3063648cefcba56cc1459adbf7e355eb69f1c38bf434e2","created_at":"2026-03-03T14:47:34Z","created_by":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Create nanobot/admin/ module with an AdminServer class backed by aiohttp.\n\nDeliverables:\n- nanobot/admin/__init__.py\n- nanobot/admin/server.py — AdminServer(config: Config) with start()/stop() methods\n  - aiohttp Application setup\n  - Bearer token middleware: reads Authorization header, returns 401 if token mismatch (only when config.gateway.admin.token is set)\n  - CORS policy (MUST be exact — do NOT use wildcard origins):\n    - Allowed origins: http://127.0.0.1:18791 and http://localhost:18791 only\n    - Access-Control-Allow-Origin: set to the request Origin only if it matches one of the two allowed origins; otherwise omit the header\n    - Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, PUT, POST, DELETE, OPTIONS\n    - Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Authorization, Content-Type\n    - Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: false (bearer token in Authorization header makes the credentials flag unnecessary)\n    - Rationale: a wildcard CORS policy (Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *) would allow any website the user visits to silently read or overwrite config via cross-site requests\n  - Serves static admin UI from nanobot/admin/static/index.html at GET /\n- Add aiohttp\u003e=3.9.0 to pyproject.toml dependencies\n- Integrate AdminServer into the gateway CLI command (start after channels, stop on shutdown)\n- Print admin URL to console if admin.enabled=True; if admin.token is empty also print a prominent warning (see Bantu-hjx)\n- Unit tests for auth middleware (valid token, invalid token, no-token-configured bypass) and CORS header correctness","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"Bantu-4kv","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"teakwood.dev@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Feature: Admin HTTP server with aiohttp and bearer-token auth","updated_at":"2026-03-03T17:12:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
