{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Approved and merged to main","closed_at":"2026-03-03T17:40:17Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"866d4fad4b6ace48ab73c18684737f28782058335b8f73ab4d59ce35e642c83c","created_at":"2026-03-03T14:47:50Z","created_by":"Navakanth Gandavarapu","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Implement REST API route handlers in nanobot/admin/routes.py for managing gateway configuration.\n\nEndpoints:\n- GET  /api/config                  Return sanitized config (all sensitive fields masked with '****')\n- GET  /api/providers               List providers with {name, label, has_key, api_base, is_oauth, is_local}\n- PUT  /api/providers/{name}        Update provider: {api_key?, api_base?, extra_headers?}; persists to config.json\n- GET  /api/channels                List channels with {name, enabled, summary}\n- GET  /api/channels/{name}         Full channel config dict (sensitive tokens masked)\n- PUT  /api/channels/{name}         Merge-update channel config, persist to disk\n- GET  /api/mcp                     List MCP servers with name and {command, url, tool_timeout}\n- POST /api/mcp/{name}              Create new MCP server entry\n- PUT  /api/mcp/{name}              Update existing MCP server\n- DELETE /api/mcp/{name}            Remove MCP server entry\n- GET  /api/agent                   Return agent defaults\n- PUT  /api/agent                   Update agent defaults (model, temperature, max_tokens, etc.)\n\nImplementation notes:\n- Concurrency safety (REQUIRED): Declare a module-level lock in routes.py:\n    _config_lock: asyncio.Lock = asyncio.Lock()\n  Every write handler MUST acquire this lock before loading config and hold it until after save_config() returns:\n    async with _config_lock:\n        cfg = load_config()\n        # ... mutate cfg ...\n        save_config(cfg)\n  This prevents concurrent PUT requests from racing and silently discarding each other's changes.\n- All reads go through load_config(); all writes call save_config() after validation, wrapped in _config_lock\n- Sensitive field masking: any key containing 'token', 'key', 'secret', 'password', 'credential' → '****'\n- Validation: invalid JSON body → 400; unknown provider → 404; unknown channel → 404\n- Unit tests for each endpoint group: providers CRUD, channels CRUD, mcp CRUD, agent settings; include a concurrency test that fires two simultaneous PUTs and verifies both changes are persisted","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"Bantu-fti","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"teakwood.dev@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Feature: Config REST API endpoints for admin console","updated_at":"2026-03-03T17:40:17Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
